The paper deals with the decidability of first-order theories over the reals, which is a topic in logic and computability theory. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of numerical methods, which suggests that it may be relevant to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.SC (Symbolic Computation). The mention of algorithms and complexity classes suggests that cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) may also be relevant sub-categories.
